parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel overflow from the filler neck can cause a fire hazard, damage to the vehicle's paint and surrounding surfaces, and create a slippery surface, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Fuel spills or sprays out of the filler neck when the tank is filled
even when the pump shuts off
resulting in a puddle of fuel on the ground and potentially damaging the vehicle's paint and surrounding surfaces.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Takata airbag inflator can cause the airbag to deploy unexpectedly, leading to injuries or fatalities. The delay in repairing the recall can also lead to a higher risk of accidents.
symptoms: failure of airbag to deploy in a crash
injuries or fatalities due to airbag malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in receiving parts for the Takata airbag recall can lead to a prolonged period of risk for drivers and passengers, increasing the likelihood of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Delay in receiving parts for recall repair
inability to schedule repair due to part unavailability
lack of communication from dealerships or manufacturers regarding part availability.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Overflow/Fuel Spray During Refueling
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel tank overflow/fuel spray during refueling can cause a fire hazard, damage to the vehicle and surrounding property, and create a safety risk for the driver and bystanders.
symptoms: Fuel spills out of the filler neck when the tank is filled
fuel sprays out of the filler neck when the pump shuts off
fuel overflows from the inlet when fueling the vehicle
fuel spills out of the tank when the fuel pump is inserted
fuel leaks from the fuel tank.
